parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can lead to weakened structural integrity, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Excessive rust and corrosion on the frame
fuel tank straps
and undercarriage
resulting in holes
cracking
and weakening of the structure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and bulging of the inner fender can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, affecting its crashworthiness and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cracks
bulges
and tears on the inner fender
particularly in the crumple zones
resulting in compromised structural integrity and potential safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS pulsates or kicks in unnecessarily
the brake pedal pulsates or vibrates
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward
the brakes do not engage properly
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper and piston can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake caliper and piston bind or stick
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt stays loose over the chest
the seat belt does not click into place
the seat belt is fully extended and will not retract
the seat belt retractor is rusted internally
the seat belt retractor spring is broken.
